          <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">disomic</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">aneuploids</ENAMEX> tend to lose the extra chromosome or
          <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">chromosomes</ENAMEX> and become haploid [ <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">45</TIMEX> ] . We therefore
          determined the frequencies of spore viability and meiotic
          diploidy as genetic measures of chromosome segregation
